The evidence with the title 'History of African Americans in Chicago - Wikipedia ' says The history of African Americans in Chicago dates back to Jean Baptiste Point Du Sable 's trading activities in the 1780s. Du Sable is the city's founder. Fugitive slaves and freedmen established the city 's first black community in the 1840s. By the late 19th century , the first black person had been elected to office.  ... . " Chicago was the most accessible northern city for African Americans in  ... 
